@startuml
title Flare-On CTF Security Flow - Malware and Exploitation Sequence

actor Attacker
participant "Remote C2 Server" as C2
participant "Malware (induct)" as Malware
participant "Custom VM" as VM
participant "Anti-Debug Thread" as AntiDebug
participant "Persistence Thread" as Persistence
participant "Network Thread" as Network
participant "File System" as FS
participant "Crontab" as Cron
database "Encrypted Files\n(*.broken)" as EncFiles

actor "Security Analyst" as Analyst
participant "SSHD Server" as SSHD
participant "liblzma\n(Compromised)" as LZMA
participant "Shellcode" as Shellcode
participant "Core Dump" as CoreDump
participant "Smart Contract\n(Binance TestNet)" as Contract
participant "UEFI App" as UEFI
participant "Encrypted\nFilesystem" as EncFS

actor "Mobile User" as MobileUser
participant "Android App\n(Swip3r)" as AndroidApp
participant "Windows Mobile App" as WinMobileApp
participant "MrBurns.jpg" as ImageData
participant "Garbage.jpg\n(Encrypted)" as EncImage

== Malware Attack Phase ==

Attacker -> Malware: Execute malware binary
activate Malware

Malware -> Malware: Check for debugger/VM
activate AntiDebug
AntiDebug -> Malware: Anti-debugging checks
deactivate AntiDebug

Malware -> Persistence: Initialize persistence mechanism
activate Persistence
Persistence -> Cron: Add crontab entry
Cron --> Persistence: Persistence established
deactivate Persistence

Malware -> Network: Initialize UDP/IRC communication
activate Network
Network -> C2: Connect via UDP
C2 --> Network: C2 commands
Network -> Malware: Relay commands
deactivate Network

Malware -> VM: Load custom VM
activate VM
VM -> VM: Decode encryption "potions"
VM -> VM: Execute obfuscated logic
VM --> Malware: Encryption routine ready
deactivate VM

Malware -> FS: Scan Documents folder
activate FS
FS --> Malware: File list
deactivate FS

loop For each target file
    Malware -> VM: Execute encryption potion
    activate VM
    VM -> VM: Apply layered encryption
    VM -> FS: Write encrypted file
    activate FS
    FS -> EncFiles: Create *.broken file
    deactivate FS
    VM --> Malware: File encrypted
    deactivate VM
end

Malware -> C2: Report encryption status
C2 --> Malware: Acknowledge
deactivate Malware

== SSHD Exploitation Phase ==

Attacker -> SSHD: Send malicious SSH request
activate SSHD
SSHD -> LZMA: Process request via liblzma
activate LZMA
LZMA -> LZMA: Trigger vulnerability
LZMA -> Shellcode: Inject and execute shellcode
activate Shellcode
Shellcode -> SSHD: Compromise SSHD process
deactivate Shellcode

SSHD -> CoreDump: Process crashes (exploitation)
activate CoreDump
CoreDump -> CoreDump: Capture memory state
deactivate CoreDump
deactivate LZMA

Analyst -> CoreDump: Analyze core dump
activate CoreDump
CoreDump --> Analyst: Extract ECC keys
deactivate CoreDump

Analyst -> Analyst: Apply Pohlig-Hellman attack
Analyst -> Contract: Query Binance TestNet
activate Contract
Contract --> Analyst: Smart contract data
deactivate Contract

Analyst -> UEFI: Extract custom UEFI app
activate UEFI
UEFI -> UEFI: Execute custom decryption command
UEFI -> EncFS: Decrypt filesystem
activate EncFS
EncFS --> UEFI: Decrypted data
deactivate EncFS
UEFI --> Analyst: Flag retrieved
deactivate UEFI
deactivate SSHD

== Mobile App Exploitation Phase ==

MobileUser -> AndroidApp: Launch app
activate AndroidApp
AndroidApp -> AndroidApp: Initialize gesture handler

loop Swipe sequence
    MobileUser -> AndroidApp: Perform swipe gesture
    AndroidApp -> AndroidApp: Process swipe in MainActivity
    AndroidApp -> AndroidApp: Validate sequence
end

AndroidApp --> MobileUser: Flag (partial)
deactivate AndroidApp

MobileUser -> WinMobileApp: Launch Windows Mobile app
activate WinMobileApp
WinMobileApp -> WinMobileApp: Verify device information
WinMobileApp -> WinMobileApp: Check device ID/hash

WinMobileApp -> ImageData: Load MrBurns.jpg
activate ImageData
ImageData --> WinMobileApp: Image data for key derivation
deactivate ImageData

WinMobileApp -> WinMobileApp: Derive XOR key from device info + image
WinMobileApp -> EncImage: Load Garbage.jpg
activate EncImage
EncImage --> WinMobileApp: Encrypted image data
deactivate EncImage

WinMobileApp -> WinMobileApp: XOR decrypt with derived key
WinMobileApp --> MobileUser: Flag revealed
deactivate WinMobileApp

== Defense Analysis Phase ==

Analyst -> Malware: Static analysis (IDA/Ghidra)
activate Malware
Malware --> Analyst: Obfuscated code structure
deactivate Malware

Analyst -> Analyst: Deobfuscate strings
Analyst -> Analyst: Identify VM opcodes

Analyst -> VM: Reverse VM instruction set
activate VM
VM --> Analyst: Encryption algorithm logic
deactivate VM

Analyst -> EncFiles: Attempt decryption
activate EncFiles
Analyst -> Analyst: Reverse layered encryption
Analyst -> Analyst: Apply decryption scripts
EncFiles --> Analyst: Flag recovered
deactivate EncFiles

@enduml
